main event: A witness spotted an unidentified fast-moving object flying between them and the moon in Rolesville, North Carolina on February 8, 1962.
interesting points: The object was flying at a high altitude in a northern direction at a 25-degree angle.
The object was moving at a very fast speed, so fast the witness could hardly keep up with it.
The witness believed the object might have been a jet plane, but was not certain.
There is a separate Project 10073 record card that mentions a ground-visual and ground-radar sighting of an unidentified object on February 12, 1962 in Rolesville, North Carolina.
The Project 10073 record card indicates the case was listed as having insufficient data.
sighted object: an unidentified fast-moving object flying between the witness and the moon
photographs: no photographs included in the report
